Wildflower & Patchwork

metadata.name: The Voyage #188
metadata.description:
The more we explore, the more things we realize there are to be explored. The more questions we find answers to, the more answers we find that require the right questions to be asked.

What is there beyond the edge of knowledge; what was, when things were none?

Will it be our body or our mind to discover that first?

And so The Voyage begins...

* * *

Press R to hide/show cosmic rain (takes a few seconds).
Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #338
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side

metadata.name: redline #78
metadata.description:
This is my second generative art project on fxhash. I wanted a project that offered more VARIETY compared for my first project so this is what I came up with: a clean and simple rectangles & lines project :D 

There are a few options for the number of columns that are generated: 3, 5, 7, 9, and each column is randomly filled with dense or alternating line patterns (sometimes no pattern!). 3 columns are common, the rest are less common. Having more than half the columns empty is relatively rare. Having all columns empty is extremely rare! 

Also I have to give credit to Tyler Hobbs, this piece was super inspired by an old IG post of his. Please enjoy!

metadata.name: Thread Cascade #278
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free only for 8 hours, for all the holders of "Laser Paintings" and "Beam"!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 10:45 CEST [UTC+2] on the 4th of July 
(example: user holds 3 "Laser Paintings" and 2 "Beam", will be able to mint "Thread Cascade" 5 times)

WARINING: The reserves will expire 8h after the drop! (at 18:45 CEST [UTC+2] on the 4th of July) And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

add ?ratio=n:n to the url to change the piece ratio (replace 'n' with a positive integer, like '?ratio=4:3')

metadata.name: FluxMongers #5
metadata.description:
FluxMongers are very old beings from another dimension and their spin produces huge amounts of energy and this energy discharge is what causes the realities of MAGNETIK to be distorted or even to be torn apart. Their ethereal nature, speed and might make their movements almost to be perceived as some kind of choreography but this can only be called a dance of destruction. What you are looking at is a frame frozen in their deadly dance…

FluxMongers were inspired by light paintings where the painter uses one or few sources of light to draw in the air very quickly and the drawing is captured by long exposure.

After going live,

- press ‘1’ to get a hi-res version and ‘2’ to get a medium-res version (hopefully it will work :/)

- press 's' to save a png

metadata.name: Cradle #265
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.

metadata.description:
* fixed version * 

Lush Fields puts you in a space far from home,fluffy,lush grass under you ... and lots of space in front of you.

Lush Fields was created as an offshoot from upcoming works, because the minimalistic focus on the grass, light and brushy haptics has a charm on its own.

Still there are lots of parameters which can change.. colours, direction of light, positions, variety
 Of the ground modulations etc.

I hope you have a good mint .. and if you are not satisfied: try another one :)
